      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Problem Section -->
    <section class="py-20 px-6 border-t border-white/5">
      <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
        <div class="backdrop-blur-xl bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/[0.08] rounded-3xl p-12 md:p-16 animate-on-scroll" style="animation: animationIn 0.8s ease-out 0.5s forwards; animation-play-state: paused;">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-red-500 to-red-700 flex items-center justify-center">
              <iconify-icon icon="ph:warning-light" class="text-2xl text-white"></iconify-icon>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">The Traffic Problem</h2>
          </div>
          
          <div class="space-y-6 text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed text-lg">
            <p>
              You spent good money on a beautiful website. It has all the right tools—forms, calendars, booking systems. 
              But there's one problem: <span class="text-white font-semibold">nobody's seeing it.</span>
            </p>
            <p>
              Even well-built sites with great functionality don't generate results if they're invisible to your target audience. 
              You need traffic—not just any traffic, but <span class="text-purple-300 font-semibold">qualified visitors</span> who are actively looking for what you offer.
            </p>
            <p class="text-white font-semibold text-xl">
              That's where we come in.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Our Approach -->
    <section class="py-20 px-6">
